body.description: 2-in-1 Comfort & SecurityThe Chicco MyFit harness + belt-positioning car seat is designed to grow with your child from a toddler car seat to a big kid booster, easily transitioning from forward-facing 5-point harness to vehicle seat belt. Nine headrest positions accommodate growth throughout both modes and work together with a 4-position recline to support proper posture. An extra-deep ErgoBoost seat with dual-density foam padding is sloped and contoured for superior comfort.Reassuring ProtectionDuoGuard provides two layers of protection with a rigid shell and EPS energy-absorbing foam that surround the head and torso. The seat shell is also reinforced with a steel frame for superior impact protection while remaining a slim car seat.Easiest to InstallThe MyFit booster seat for car is designed with smart functionality that makes it the easiest to install simply, accurately and securely—every time. A 4-position ReclineSure leveling system and RideRight bubble levels help achieve and verify a proper angle in the vehicle seat. Premium LATCH connectors and a LockSure belt-tightening system with wide routing make it easy to achieve a tight and secure fit with LATCH or the vehicle seat belt.User-Friendly TouchpointsA padded, no-rethread harness with a one-pull tightener provides reassuring security for growing toddlers. The harness easily hides away to create a belt-positioning grow with me car seat with shoulder and lap belt guides for big kids four years and up. Two dishwasher-safe CupFolders feature easy push-button removal and fold out of the way to save space when not in use for a convenient travel car seat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I still remember 18 years ago when my sister used Chicco everything, including fine carseats for her children.I chose Chicco because it's the only brand I trust. It's very comfortable for a child, and it's great for any weather. My daughter never complained of being uncomfortable in the seat. It feels more of quality and protects the child more than the other brand seats that I worked with. That's why in case of an accident my Daughter will be safe 👍🏻. It's easy to clean the seat, I washed the fabric several times and it still looks brand new. I love the luxurious smart design of this car seat, it's very user friendly. I've been using this car seat for years and it's the best car seat I used for my child. I dare say it's a great buy and the car seat is worth every penny, because it lasts and after long use it still looks as if I bought it yesterday. When you use the Chicco brand you will never go back.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is my second one of these seats. The first one was for my car and I ended up buying a second one for my husbands truck. When my daughter falls asleep her head does not fall forward, it stays back and she stays comfortable. Easy to install and my daughter loves it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Only carseat I'll ever have to buy
reviews.reviewText: I bought 2 of these for my twin boys after they started growing out of their first ones that they had as small babies. Although these were on the pricier side, I wanted something that would fit them comfortably now and would also be something they could grow into.They are very bulky, but I liked that. They have arm rests and each come with 2 cup holders. You can remove the cup holders if you want just one on each or if you'd prefer not to have them at all. There is a small level on the side that shows you how much the seat is angled and there are instructions telling you what is appropriate for either harness mode or booster mode. There are 4 levels of recline and 9 positions for the headrest to keep kids comfortable.The harness is easy to use comfortable for my boys. It really does feel like they are safe in this carseat. The hooks to anchor it into the seats are also easy to use. There is a button to release so you don't have to try and use those clamps like with other seats. I really love this carseat and my boys love them as well. I highly recommend as a mother who wants to feel her babies are safe.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: We got this for our road trip, our son was due for an upgrade and this got amazing reviews, as it should. It’s so comfortable, he even fell asleep in it (and still does). Lots of space! And his head doesn’t fall forward when he sleeps. It is very sturdy and very safe. I feel at ease when he is in the seat. We even convinced his grandparents to return another brand they’d just bought to get this one instead. So well built! Highly recommend, it’s worth the price for peace of mind and comfort for your child.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Product snd customer satisfaction
reviews.reviewText: I bought the car seat for my 2-1/2 year granddaughter because she’s outgrown her baby car seat. I love the accommodating headrest so that her head doesn’t hang like her other Gracco car seat , the installation ease and most importantly the roomy buckling belt. There’s enough room for her to move her legs and not feel too constrained. The Gracco brand was getting hard to close around her legs. I know she’ll be using this car seat for a very long time (weight capacity is 35-100 lbs). My granddaughter and I love it and that makes me very happy. I will be ordering a 2nd car seat. Note: please do your research, watch any YouTube videos before making your purchase. I highly recommend this product!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Overall the seat is great - it is comfortable for my five year old, fits in the car, and is easy enough to install. I dropped a star because the harness straps are more difficult for my five year old to navigate (and me honestly) than his past Britax Marathon seat. Especially the cover for the crotch buckle - it really gets in the way. Overall I would still recommend the seat but I don’t like it as much as the Britax, which he’s unfortunately outgrown.
